6:
I beg your pardon? These are the
finest gems that Mirea has to offer!
What do you mean, you won't
accept them?
9:
Fine. Would you be willing to take
this halberd as a substitute? It is
impeccably sharp, sure to cut down
all your enemies!
12:
I don't need gems or weapons, lady,
I need MONEY. Fork it over already!
15: What seems to be the problem here?
18:
The problem is this girl is trying to
pay for her meal with... jewels or
something! And she's being
stubborn about it!
21:
I'll have you know that these gems
are perfectly fine legal tender in the
great and proud nation of Mirea!
Why would you refuse them?!
25:
Looks to me like a sheltered princess
who doesn't get how the real world
works.
30:
Yeah... But I'd rather this didn't
escalate further, so I'll just go ahead
and pay her bill.
37:
Your name was Alk, correct? I
wanted to extend my formal
gratitude for your deed back there.
40:
My name is Toria... You really saved
me from a potentially dangerous
situation. Thank you.
42:
However... I remain skeptical.
Why did you choose to help me?
45:
Well... I kind of felt bad for the
shopkeeper...
50:
A likely story! But do not think that
you can deceive me, Alk! I see
through your lies and deception!
52:
For I am the first princess of the
kingdom of Mirea! You knew this
much, did you not? That is why you
chose to help me!
57:
Guess I was right about you being a
princess. Figures.
The hell is a Mirea though? Never
heard of that.
62:
Y-you what?! How could you
possibly not know of Mirea?!
66:
Ahem. In that case, allow me to
explain! The great kingdom of Mirea
is my home and native land!
69:
It is a... modestly-sized country that
lies on the farthest ends of the land
between the Farlands and Palpebra!
73:
Huh... I see... If you don't mind me
asking, what is the princess of Mirea
doing in Palpebra, exactly?
77:
I'm obviously here on official
diplomatic business—I intend to
carefully monitor this wicked state
which so threatens my homeland!
82:
In what ways is Palpebra "wicked," 
if I may ask?
85:
It's simple! Fifty years ago, this city
was nothing but an empty
wasteland. Yet now, it pretends to
be a thriving metropolis!
89:
As such, it siphons away people
from nearby lands, growing its own
population year by year.
93:
One of those lands being my very
own! It is not enough that our
territory is... limited in scope—our
populace too is now dwindling!
98:
Yeah, rural depopulation is a serious
problem...
101:
R-rural?! Do not speak of us as if we
are some backwater village! We
merely have a more... minimalist
mindset than other countries.
105:
Regardless! That is why I am firm in
my determination to CONQUER
Palpebra.
Or... I want to... but...
109:
Your food is superb, and the scenery
breathtaking! Your streets are filled
with stores and entertainment—I'm
at a loss for what to do first!
114: I am glad you're having fun.
118:
Yes, that's all well and good, but we
certainly can't have you recklessly
spend all your money away as you
have been.
123:
I... do admit I may have gone too far
in a few places...
127:
Well, you seem to be done with your
sightseeing—I mean, "monitoring"...
How about just packing up and
going home?
132:
I cannot! For you see, I have made a
promise not to return until I recover
all of Mirea's sacred relics!
141:
Indeed. They are the pride and joy of
Mirea, and—
145:
Thief! Someone catch that man,
please!
149: Huh? Wait, Toria, what are you—
153:
Even on this wretched Palpebran
soil, the law is the law!
156:
You're in my way. Move it, or I'll cut
you into pieces!
158:
Thank you for your consideration,
but I fear it is misplaced. I am not a
weak little princess that needs to be
protected.
170:
Please do not misunderstand! It's
just that those of the Mirean royal
family tend to be... more powerful
than the commonfolk!
175:
Ah... To think that I would put on
such a shameful display in vile
Palpebra of all places!
178: It wasn't shameful. It was very cool.
182:
Yeah, that was actually incredible!
Plus, you got some thank-you
money from it too—seems like a win
to me.
185:
I suppose so... At least I won't want
for lodging tonight...
189:
W-wait a moment! What happened
to my wallet? It's missing!
191:
Is this the work of one of those
Palpebran "shifts" I've heard so
much about?!
195:
Uh, no, you probably just got
pickpocketed. Or dropped it.
200:
How could that be?! Where will I
spend the night now?!
217:
*sigh* There she goes again, letting
anyone in.
221:
I am most grateful for all your help!
Though we only just met, you've
treated me so kindly...
224:
You truly are like the Legendary Four
from the Mirean epics!
231:
Yes! They are said to have helped
our nation overcome great
tribulations in the past!
235:
There is no further doubt in my
mind—you ARE the Legendary Four!
239:
All we did was pay your bill and offer
you a place to stay, I don't know
about—
242:
Come! We will take down Palpebra
TOGETHER!
